<TEXT>
<P>
The Nov. 9 episode of "The Cosby Show" was one of the funniest shows I have 
ever seen and is destined to become a classic. Obviously, Florence Burks and 
Dorothy Dexter of Simi Valley (Viewers' Views, Dec. 3) have no sense of humor 
or have totally missed the point. Cliff Huxtable is an obstetrician who sees 
pregnant women all the time. Who else could empathize so well with the foibles 
of pregnancy and childbirth? Lighten up, ladies. 
</P>
<P>
Marlene Silver, Encino 
</P>
</TEXT>
