<HEADLINE>
<P>
STOP MILKEN BASHING, AT LEAST UNTIL A VERDICT OF GUILT OR INNOCENCE HAS BEEN 
DETERMINED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I note a recent letter to the editor concerning Michael Milken, which stated 
that his 1987 compensation of $550 million "doesn't sound like he made it the 
old fashioned way." 
</P>
<P>
What is that supposed to mean? Have we gotten to the point where we now presume 
someone is a crook if they're successful? 
</P>
<P>
I do not have access to all of the facts and evidence concerning the Milken 
case. Neither does the letter writer. I don't know whether Milken is guilty. 
Neither does the letter writer. 
</P>
<P>
I do, however, presume his innocence. And I am extremely offended by someone 
who, based solely on what they understand to be Milken's compensation, implies 
that he is rich, so he must be guilty. 
</P>
<P>
RANDY YOUNG 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 
</P>
</TEXT>
