<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOESKY FURLOUGH PROVES JUSTICE TRULY IS BLIND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is with a degree of cynicism that I write this letter. On Nov. 16, a picture 
of poor Ivan Boesky appeared in the business section. 
</P>
<P>
Hollywood buffs will immediately notice that his appearance bears some 
resemblance to the late great yachtsman and movie star, Sterling Hayden. Please 
note that clutched in the prison-hardened left hand is a pair of yachting deck 
shoes and jeans. In the right hand appears to be a soft bag, the type sailors 
use for weekend yachting. 
</P>
<P>
Prison has indeed changed Mr. Boesky. Madam justice may be blind, but in 
white-collar crimes, she appears to have a taste for the good life. 
</P>
<P>
CLARENCE C. GRAHAM JR. 
</P>
<P>
Whittier 
</P>
