<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOESKY FURLOUGH PROVES JUSTICE TRULY IS BLIND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I picked up (the Nov. 16) Times and, smirking back at me is a picture of Ivan 
Boesky as he appeared on his most recent furlough from federal prison. It's 
difficult to say whether my dominant emotion at that moment was embarrassment 
or disgust. 
</P>
<P>
What are we doing furloughing Ivan Boesky -- or any other criminal? 
</P>
<P>
This man is in prison, for crying out loud! For felonies. Essentially, he stole 
from people. And our response is, "Hey, Ivan, take a week off. Go home. Visit 
the family. You're cool, guy." 
</P>
<P>
BILL BEDSWORTH 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 
</P>
