<HEADLINE>
<P>
A HAVEN FOR GAY TEENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am glad to see that youth troubled with their sexuality are being given help 
in today's school system. The recent Report of the Secretary's Task Force on 
Youth Suicide clearly pointed out that gay and lesbian youth are two to three 
times more likely to commit suicide. 
</P>
<P>
The fact that Secretary of Health and Human Services Louis Sullivan and George 
Bush chose to ignore these statistics is appalling. In a memo to William 
Dannemeyer (R-Calif.) on Sept. 7, Sullivan said any attention to the problem 
would run contrary to strengthening the institution of the family. 
</P>
<P>
In my opinion, anything that keeps children from committing suicide sides with 
family values. For an Administration that wants to uphold the sanctity of life, 
this response was uncaring and sadly ironic. 
</P>
<P>
DALE GRINER 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
