<HEADLINE>
<P>
A HAVEN FOR GAY TEENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I strongly agree that there should be some sort of program that accurately 
addresses teen-age sexuality. But it infuriates me that our tax dollars are 
being used to outright promote homosexuality. Virginia Uribe is not only a 
proud lesbian, but a gay rights activist as well. How can a program founded and 
operated by a lesbian activist be fair and unbiased? I am appalled that there 
is even a debate as to whether this program is converting confused individuals 
into proud homosexuals. 
</P>
<P>
DAMON CARRON 
</P>
<P>
Norwalk 
