<P>
GET IN THE SWING WITH NEW GLIDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE ELLINGSON, Ellingson has been designing patterns and plans for the 
amateur woodworker since 1948. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
You can swing day or night, alone or in a group, with our elegant canopy glider 
swing. A combination of all the best features found in outdoor gliders, it 
seats up to four adults, has a table for holding your drinks, the canopy shades 
you from direct sunlight and it has a gentle swinging motion. Best of all, it's 
easy to build when using our step-by-step plan. 
</P>
<P>
Measuring about 94 inches high and 93 1/2 inches deep, it's more than 6 1/2 
feet wide. The glider is built from fir, plywood and galvanized pipe. First, 
build the frame and install the pipe, then add the seats, canopy and table (if 
desired). A materials list, cutting schedule, detailed directions with photos 
and diagrams will guide you. Traceable patterns for all pieces that are not 
straight cuts are also included. 
</P>
