<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMPASSION APPRECIATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On Friday I got the news of a death in the family, occurring in Des Moines. The 
funeral was to be Monday. I called three airlines: American, United and America 
West. They all serve Des Moines from Los Angeles. Of the three, only American 
offered me a compassionate fare for flying on Sunday and returning on Tuesday. 
This fare was less than half the regular (not weekend) fare. And when I picked 
up my ticket at American, the clerk was very solicitous and expressed real 
concern for me and the trip I was taking. 
</P>
<P>
I can best express my appreciation by informing others of this courtesy. 
</P>
<P>
DONN R. SCHOENMANN 
</P>
<P>
Glendale 
</P>
</TEXT>
