<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEPALI CLIMBER DIES ON SLOPES OF EVEREST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KATMANDU, Nepal 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nepali climber Finjoo Sherpa died of altitude sickness during a South Korean 
attempt to ascend Mt. Everest, the world's highest mountain, Nepali officials 
said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The Nepali Tourism Ministry said the 41-year-old climber died as he was being 
taken down the 29,028-foot mountain from a camp at 20,800 feet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
