<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONDO FIRE DISPLACES FOUR FAMILIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A two-alarm blaze damaged a four-unit condominium complex Saturday morning, 
forcing four families to seek temporary housing, San Diego Fire Department 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire started at 5:02 a.m. in the garage of the complex at 2818 Terrace 
Pines Drive. San Diego officials requested help from the Chula Vista Fire 
Department to battle the swift-moving blaze. 
</P>
<P>
The fire reached the attic and caused about $200,000 in damage to the building 
and $100,000 in damage to belongings. 
</P>
<P>
The American Red Cross is providing temporary housing to one of the three 
displaced families. The couple, along with their 12-year-old daughter and 
5-year-old son, do not expect to return to their gutted home for the holidays 
and are temporarily in a motel, said Red Cross spokesman Dave Ricks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
