<HEADLINE>
<P>
UCLA WOMEN PLAY TENNESSEE TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PETE THOMAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tennessee, the defending NCAA women's basketball champion, will begin a series 
of games against Southern California teams today against UCLA at 2 at Pauley 
Pavilion. 
</P>
<P>
The Bruins have not fared well against the Volunteers, having lost 10 of 11 
games overall and seven straight since beating them during the 1980-81 season. 
</P>
<P>
Tennessee (5-1) had its 22-game winning streak snapped Dec. 9 by Louisiana 
Tech, 59-58, and was replaced by the Techsters as the nation's top-ranked team. 
UCLA (4-1) is coming off an 84-75 victory over Cal State Fullerton, during 
which guard Rehema Stephens, in her first year of eligibility after 
transferring from Colorado, scored a career-high 31 points. Stephens, a 
sophomore, averages a team-high 18.1 points a game. 
</P>
<P>
Tennessee will plays at Cal State Long Beach Tuesday and at USC Friday. PETE 
THOMAS 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
