<P>
December 17, 1989, Sunday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 21; Column 5; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
388 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
KATELLA WINS TITLE ON FREE KICK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chris Orizaba scored on a free kick at the 75th minute to break a 1-1 tie and 
give Katella High School (8-1-2) the championship of the Brea-Olinda boys' 
soccer tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Katella had tied the score at the 39th minute on a penalty kick by Brian Schenk 
after Gary Hurtarte of Bell Gardens High School had opened the scoring 10 
minutes into the game. 
</P>
<P>
In other Brea-Olinda tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
California 2, Brea-Olinda 1 (OT) -- Jeff Ortiz scored the lone goal for 
Brea-Olinda (3-4-2) at the 17th minute of the third-place match. 
</P>
<P>
Sunny Hills 1, Esperanza 0 -- Cameron Hull scored on a 25-yard kick at the 
20-minute mark to pace Sunny Hills in the consolation final. 
</P>
<P>
In nonleague boys' soccer: 
</P>
<P>
El Toro 2, Servite 1 -- Ian Doleman had both goals for El Toro (3-2), the 
second the game-winner with one minute left. 
</P>
<P>
In the Hacienda Heights Wilson boys' soccer tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 1, Diamond Bar 0 -- Cori Senko scored for Cypress (7-1-1) in a 
second-round match. In the first round, Ray Klug had both goals to lead Cypress 
to a 2-0 victory over Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
In South Torrance girls' soccer tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Edison 3, Palos Verdes 2 -- Carrie Ramirez scored a penalty kick, and goalie 
Nikki Turner had two saves of penalty kicks to lift Edison in a consolation 
semifinal match. 
</P>
<P>
In the Cerritos girls' soccer tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Marina 1, La Habra 0 -- In the fifth-place semifinal match, Wendy Gratteau 
scored for Marina (4-3-1). In an earlier game, Temple City defeated Marina, 
3-0, in championship quarterfinal. 
</P>
