<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFING: EVENTS IN THE NEWS THIS WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Holiday boat parades have become a fixture off the coast of the county the last 
few years. The Cruise of Lights in Huntington Harbour, sponsored by the 
Huntington Harbour Philharmonic, takes participants on a tour of waterfront 
homes and yachts decorated for the holidays. It begins at 5:30, 6:30, 7:30 and 
8:30 p.m. daily through Friday. The Christmas Boat Parade in Newport Harbor 
features more than 200 decorated boats. The parade starts at Collins Island and 
travels around the harbor. It is sponsored by the Newport Harbor Area Chamber 
of Commerce. Grandstand seating is available at the Sea Scout Base on West 
Coast Highway. The parade starts at 6:30 p.m. today through Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, A boat parade lights things up in Huntington Harbour. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
