<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEMORIAL: The 14 women gunned down last week at the University of Montreal will 
be memorialized at a vigil beginning at 7 p.m. today at the Unitarian Church in 
Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
CAR AUCTION: A variety of vehicles seized in drug raids will be auctioned today 
at 1 p.m in the City of Industry. The auction is being conducted at the 
headquarters of The Nationwide Companies Commercial Auction Systems. 
</P>
<P>
LAW ENFORCEMENT: Prompted to act by increasing vandalism, the Los Angeles 
County Transportation Commission on Monday will announce its $1.1-million 
contract with the Los Angeles Sheriff's Department to provide law enforcement 
along the entire 22-mile Long Beach to downtown Blue Line, now under 
construction. 
</P>
<P>
TOY DRIVE: On Thursday, Mayor Tom Bradley will join celebrities in distributing 
gifts to residents of public housing projects as part of the annual Los Angeles 
Children's Toy Drive. Toys will be distributed at 11 a.m. at Imperial Courts, 
12:30 p.m. at Nickerson Gardens, 1:30 p.m. at Hacienda Village, 2:30 p.m. at 
Jordan Downs and 3:30 p.m. at Avalon Gardens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
