<HEADLINE>
<P>
EGYPT INTERIOR MINISTER UNHURT IN BOMB BLAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CAIRO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Egyptian Interior Minister Zaki Badr survived an apparent attempt on his life 
Saturday when a truck carrying explosives blew up near his motorcade in central 
Cairo, sources said. 
</P>
<P>
Badr, who has cracked down on Islamic militants under emergency laws enabling 
people to be detained without trial, was traveling on a route he uses every 
day, the sources said. The truck exploded about 30 yards from his vehicle 
Saturday morning. No one was hurt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
