<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CANYONS BEATS MT. SAN JACINTO; STREAK HITS 10 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
College of the Canyons' women's basketball team extended its school-record 
winning streak to 10 games with a 103-46 nonconference victory over Mt. San 
Jacinto on Saturday at Canyons. Canyons (10-1) forced Mt. San Jacinto (1-8) 
into 38 turnovers. 
</P>
<P>
Canyons' Tressie Millender led all scorers with 26 points and grabbed nine 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Dawn Coleman scored 16 points, and Michelle Cabaldon tallied 13. Dominique Ice 
and Debbie Barnard came off the bench to score 14 and 12 points, respectively. 
</P>
<P>
In other women's games: 
</P>
<P>
Boise State 77, Cal State Northridge 38 -- Host Boise State, a National 
Collegiate Athletic Assn. Division I school, forced Cal State Northridge into 
40 turnovers with a tight man-to-man defense. Boise State (4-3) had 15 steals 
in the nonconference game. 
</P>
<P>
No Northridge player reached double figures in scoring. Guard Joan Weinerth 
scored a team-high nine points and added five steals. Jody Bittner, Denna 
Mulverhill and Julie Arlotto each scored eight points for Northridge (2-9). 
</P>
<P>
Pierce 84, San Diego City College 43 -- Pierce scored 20 unanswered points 
early in the game to run away with the consolation title of the Trade Tech 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Pierce (6-8) outrebounded San Diego, 54-30. Forward Carol Schoenmann pulled 
down 24 rebounds, and center Michelle Ahnstadt (14) and guard Sarah Dancs (15) 
each also had double figures in rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Southern California College 72, Occidental 71 -- Occidental trailed, 72-71, 
with 16 seconds to play and missed two potential game-winning shots in the 
closing moments of a nonconference game at Southern California College. 
</P>
<P>
Sharon Bruner scored a game-high 23 points for Occidental. 
</P>
<P>
Valley 70, Grossmont 55 -- Sandrine Rocher had 16 points, nine rebounds and 
four assists to lead Valley (8-2) to a nonconference win at Grossmont. 
</P>
<P>
UC San Diego 71, The Master's 52 -- UC San Diego's Cari Young scored a 
game-high 21 points and had nine rebounds at The Master's. 
</P>
<P>
Susie Sparks scored a team-high 16 points for The Master's (2-11). 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S 
</P>
<P>
UC San Diego 74, The Master's 69 -- UC San Diego's Tim Rapp scored a game-high 
18 points to lead his team to a nonconference win at San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
The Master's (7-6) received a team-high 15 points and 11 rebounds from Jason 
Webster and 12 points from Jeff Newton. 
</P>
</TEXT>
