<TEXT>
<P>
With regard to your Critic's Corner column on Dec. 3, I have no idea what 
section or portion of the television-viewing population I represent, but I 
disagree with the entire thrust of the piece. I thoroughly enjoy reenactments! 
I think Fox TV popularized the "simulated reenactment" concept on contemporary 
television, which would help explain what I believe is Fox's steady rise in 
grass-roots popularity of late: It knows what the public wants. My verdict is 
still out on whether reenactments are acceptable for actual, current on-air 
news items; but if they are clearly labeled, any reasonable person will accept 
them as such. 
</P>
<P>
McCall, Westchester 
</P>
</TEXT>
