<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY 1990 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More cars, new tollways, bustling universities and a host of challenges await 
residents as a bigger and more urbanized Orange County embarks on the 1990s. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
University Enrollment 
</P>
<P>
Nearly 10,000 new students are expected to enroll at the county's four-year 
institutions. 
</P>
<P>
UC Irvine 
</P>
<P>
Total graduate, undergraduate and medical students: 
</P>
<P>
1985: 13,086 
</P>
<P>
1990: 16,233 
</P>
<P>
1995: 19,507 
</P>
<P>
2000: 22,781 
</P>
<P>
Source: UCI 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton 
</P>
<P>
Total Students: 
</P>
<P>
1985: 23,227 
</P>
<P>
1990: 25,300 
</P>
<P>
1995: 27,150 
</P>
<P>
2000: 28,600 
</P>
<P>
Source: Cal State Fullerton 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Cellular Phones 
</P>
<P>
More people will be able to call the office while stuck in traffic jams. 
</P>
<P>
1989: 1,000 
</P>
<P>
1995: 3,000 
</P>
